<br>
If you pay for a piece of art it is indeed yours. However mutilating it, changing it etc would devalue the piece of art. Ownership does not grant you the right to say &quot;I made this&quot;. Go to a gallery. The paintings there give credit to the artist and to the owner they don't say the owner is the artist (unless its owned by the artist).<br>
<br>
Also the owner of the work or service gets to decide what you are paying for when you make a donation. You can't walk into Blockbuster plunk down five bucks and then leave with the entire contents of the store. Your five buck entitles you to the rental of a certain number of movies for a certain amount of time.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bygzalf>Bygzalf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:orange;'>Tavern Resident</span></span><br>  Posts: 592<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(6/10/03 9:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3262.topic&index=282>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: integrity</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Ever stop to think for maybe just a moment that 1) we farm the hell outta stuff, 2) we share a 3 way bank acct, and 3) I tradeskill my ass off. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
